OL,3,CMan, 28, found guilty of rioting in
OL,4,CEly following the death of two
OL,5,Cteenagers
OL,7,FThe court heard the riot began during
OL,8,Fthe early evening of May 22, 2023, and
OL,9,Fcontinued into the early hours of the
OL,10,Fnext day. Mr Cobbe said: "Dozens of
OL,11,Fpeople were involved. Bottles, bricks,
OL,12,Fplasterboard and more were hurled at
OL,13,Fpolice officers.
OL,15,F"Fires were set and fireworks thrown,
OL,16,Fcars were trashed, overturned and set
OL,17,Falight; a petrol bomb was thrown at an
OL,18,Fofficer, covering her in flames. It
OL,19,Fwas carnage for several hours."
