OL,3,CMan, 28, found guilty of rioting in
OL,4,CEly following the death of two
OL,5,Cteenagers
OL,7,F"He was instrumental in striking the
OL,8,Fmatch that lit the fuse. Leaving
OL,9,Fbefore the riot had fully taken hold
OL,10,Fdoes not make him any less responsible
OL,11,Ffor the part he played in this riot.
OL,12,FIt is no defence that he left before
OL,13,Fthe riot he encouraged fully took
OL,14,Fhold."
